    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Degradation of a material caused by exposure to light, specifically the chemical changes to photodegradable molecules induced by absorption of photons, especially those wavelengths found in sunlight. The process by which a material is damaged due to prolonged exposure to ultraviolet radiation.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
